body:
If a generate loop has a call to a constant function inside, e.g.:
for (i = 0; i < log2(BUFS + 1); i = i + 1) ...
The compiler aborts with (latest git):
ivl: elab_scope.cc:1174: bool PGenerate::generate_scope_loop_(Design*, NetScope*): Assertion `test' failed.
Aborted

If the result of the constant function is first assigned to a parameter, e.g.:
parameter BUF2 = log2(BUFS + 1);
for (i = 0; i < BUF2; i = i + 1) ...
the compiler operates as expected and no assertion is hit.

A full testcase representing the issue is as follows:
--cut--
module test;

parameter [16 - 1:0] BUFS = 16'd1;

function integer log2;
input integer x;

integer i;
begin 
        i = 0; 
        while ((1 << i) < x)
                i = i + 1;
        log2 = i;
end
endfunction

wire [16 - 1:0] buf_seqno;
wire [log2(BUFS + 1) - 1:0] buf_seqno_gray;

genvar j;

generate 
        for (j = 0; j < log2(BUFS + 1); j = j + 1)
                assign buf_seqno_gray[j] = ^buf_seqno[log2(BUFS[(0 * 16)+:16] + 1) - 1:j];
endgenerate

endmodule
--cut--
